The paper proposes a self-supervised attention network for image clustering, which involves deep learning techniques for computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular research area in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for image clustering, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves the use of large-scale image datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
